Question: Describe winter season in your hometown (do not disclose the name of your hometown).
Answer:
in my hometown, the weather is very damp. so even the temperature is not very low, you still feel very cold. there is about two to three snows each winter, but they wont last long like in north usually a few hours or one day and it melts very fast too. the lows can be negative ten C and highs can be ten to fifteen C. the worst is rainning in winter, you would feel freezing cold and very upset if you do not have a car.